HEADWORD: Alpestrine
<hw>Al*pes"trine</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Alpestris</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to the Alps, or
other high mountains; <as>as, <ex>Alpestrine</ex> diseases,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Growing on the elevated parts of
mountains, but not above the timber line; subalpine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alpha</ent>⟦br⟧
